// Test file for keyword migration
// Contains both mathematical expressions and English prose

TEXT: This is a simple example and demonstration of the migration tool.
TEXT: The system should not replace English words in prose text.

// Mathematical expression - should be migrated
p and q => p

TRUTH TABLE:
p | q | p and q | p or q | not p
T | T | T       | T      | F
T | F | F       | T      | F
F | T | F       | T      | T
F | F | F       | F      | T

EQUIV:
p and (q or r)
<=> (p and q) or (p and r) [distributivity]
<=> not (not p or (not q and not r)) [De Morgan]

TEXT: The formula p or q is a disjunction, and the formula not p is a negation.
TEXT: Both formulas are important concepts in propositional logic.

axdef
  validPassword : P String
where
  forall pw : String |
    pw in validPassword <=>
      # pw >= 8 and
      (exists d : 0..9 | intToString(d) in pw) and
      not (pw = "password" or pw = "12345678")
end

TEXT: Note that the password must be strong and secure, not weak or common.
